{
  "_readme": [
    "Targets for the nightly source-monitor (scripts/source-monitor.mjs). PURE DATA \u2014",
    "extending coverage of the monitor = appending an entry here, never editing the script.",
    "",
    "Two lists:",
    "  \u2022 reprobe[] \u2014 sources previously REJECTED (dead / stale / frozen / blocked / broken /",
    "    polygon-only) with the exact endpoint that was probed and the rejection receipt.",
    "    The monitor re-probes each one nightly; if it has come back to life AND passes the",
    "    fail-closed auto-wire gate, it is wired automatically. Source of these receipts:",
    "    docs/source-registry.md 'Rejected' sections (2026-07-13 Texas passes).",
    "  \u2022 discovery[] \u2014 jurisdictions currently on the facility floor (modeled ZIP pages,",
    "    no development feed). Each carries its OFFICIAL first-party catalog endpoints only.",
    "    The monitor walks these catalogs for permit/land-use layers and evaluates candidates",
    "    through the same gate. NEVER add a search-engine or third-party aggregator here.",
    "",
    "hosts[] is a per-target allowlist: a candidate layer is only ever wired if its URL host",
    "is in the target's allowlist. This is what stops the documented lookalike trap (the",
    "'Building_Permits' hits that were actually Brampton, ON and Atlanta, GA data \u2014",
    "docs/source-registry.md, slc-planning-petitions receipts).",
    "",
    "coverage is HUMAN-PINNED per target (state + county of the jurisdiction). The monitor",
    "never derives coverage from data \u2014 a wired entry inherits it verbatim."
  ],
